comment_data.body:
Instead of coding the name back and forth, we might actually get away with this:
```C
if (method_name && PyUnicode_ReadChar(method_name, 3) == 'r') {
    // This is enough to distinguish the "iter*" names from "items", "values", "keys".
    method_name = PyUnicode_Substring(method_name, 4, 10);  // longest is "itervalues" (len=10)
}
```
Plus error handling for both calls, plus refcount cleanup for `method_name`.
(I'm aware that UTF-8 encoding should be cheap in PyPy, but unpacking the string buffer for an undetermined lifetime might not be.)

